President Donald Trump has announced his intention to nominate Dan R. Brouillette as Deputy Secretary of Energy for the Department of Energy. Brouillette is currently the Senior Vice President and head of public policy for USAA, a leading financial services provider for the military community. He has also held positions at Ford Motor Company, the United States House of Representatives Committee on Energy and Commerce, and the Department of Energy. Brouillette is a former state energy regulator and a U.S. Army veteran. He and his wife have nine children and reside in San Antonio, Texas.